cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.NA, cs.Distributed Computing. 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with geometric spanners and Delaunay triangulations, which are fundamental concepts in computational geometry. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes an algorithm to compute a subgraph of the Delaunay triangulation. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed Computing) is another possible category as the paper also proposes a distributed algorithm to compute the same bounded degree planar spanner. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible category as the paper involves computing the spanning ratio of the Delaunay triangulation. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) is less likely as the paper does not focus on visualization or rendering of geometric objects.
